<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-126-116 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 041 317</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Executive  Summer 1991 v4 n3 p41(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Quality communications: the key to control. (software development)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poole, Bernard John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Communications are the key to successful software developmentenvironments.andP;  Managers of software application and developmentprojects can improve the quality of communication and achieve anincreased level of control; knowledge is power.andP;  SoftwareConfiguration Management is the most important aspect of controlof software design projects.andP;  The configuration management team isresponsible for maintaining clean, secure, ordered access to thecomplete set of configuration items.andP;  Data dictionaries, changerequests, specifications, test plans and quality assurance plansshould be centrally controlled.andP;  Estimates are that 70 percent ofthe cost of software design is invested in maintenance.andP;  Designspecifications of a software system should include a complete datadictionary and complete description of modules and inter-modularbindings.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software DesignConfigurationMISCodingCommunications ApplicationsQuality ControlSoftware ValidationGuidelinesMethods.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>